		</SENTENCE>
		<SENTENCE ID="3.2">
			<STRING>The laws that defined apartheid began to be repealed or abolished by the National Party in 1990 after a long and sometimes violent struggle (including economic sanctions from the international community) by the Black majority as well as many White, Coloured, and Indian South Africans. </STRING>
